<br>
So our &quot;allies&quot;, France and Russia, have entered into agreements with Saddam and Iraq (our enemy) which now are in jeopardy over the war we wish to wage.  And for this reason we should turn a blind eye to the threat that Saddam poses.  Perhaps we should not pursue war, and leave him to do as he pleases.<br>
<br>
Then, down the road when he develops a chemical or nuclear weapon arsenal and unleashes it at some unsuspecting country, the world will point fingers at us and say &quot;America, how could you stand by and allow that to happen?!?  You should be doing something about that!&quot;<br>
<br>
And God forbid Saddam should be foolish enough to attack directly at America.  Not indirectly through the support of terrorist organizations, or hiding behind some other guise, but full on attack us with the use of some long range weapons... Do you honestly believe we would stop to ask the UN's approval before declaring war and turning Iraq into a greasy smudge?  They would be picking pieces of Saddam out the the trees lining the streets of Paris.<br>
<br>
Do I really care whether George W. Bush's administration has succeded at foreign policy?  Not in the least.  Those countries whose opinions I am supposed to care about are motivated as much as, if not more than, the US by political and monetary concerns.  Am I supposed to believe that France and Russia object to this confilt because of Humanitarian Concerns?  Please don't insult my intelligence. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
