</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=crazylowfyrwildforge>Crazy Lowfyr Wildforge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 291<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/18/03 11:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Polling.</span><hr size=1> I don't give a shit what your poll says.<br>
<br>
Here's why:<br>
<br>
1) The opinions of the general populace don't matter.  Yeah, I live in a Democracy.  A *Representative* Democracy.  Why Representative? Because the Founding Fathers of the US, while cognizant of the fact that human beings need a certain amount of self-determination, also realized that human beings are, on whole, fucking idiots.  That's why people watched American Idol.  Because they are idiots.<br>
<br>
Yes, some of the finest American minds have made some blunders in the past on foreign policy issues.  But I can only IMAGINE the horrors that would be unleashed if Billy Bob from the Exxon in Decatur was a key factor in the decision making process.<br>
<br>
The same goes for Esteban Assbandito in Barcelona, or Pierre Le Cocksmoker in Ghey Paree.   Their opinions don't mean diddly shit.  <br>
<br>
2) Polls, commonly portrayed as scientifically accurate means of measuring trends in opinion, are about as accurate as a blind man firing a gun into Lake Superior in the hopes of killing a fish.  This is because...<br>
<br>
2a - Only a small number of people are actually polled.<br>
<br>
2b - The wording of the questions can be misleading, and produce false responses.<br>
<br>
2c - People will say things they don't believe, because they THINK that's the answer the pollster is looking for.<br>
<br>
Trust me, I have first hand knowledge of this.   In the television ratings book, people would mark down that they watched 20/20 in a distinctly higher percentage than showed up in the metered households, which are done electronically.<br>
<br>
Interestingly enough,  shows like Jerry Springer scored much lower in diaries than they did on meters.  Guilty pleasures, perhaps?<br>
<br>
Anyway, the world is opposed to war with Iraq?  Feh.  Tough shit.  In the immortal words of Benjamin Grimm, it's clobberin' time.<br>
<br>
